SIMPLE: uniaxial
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uniaxial
<hw>U`ni*ax"i*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Uni</ets> +
<ets>axial</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld>
<def>Having but one optic axis, or line of no double
refraction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In <xex>uniaxial</xex> crystals, the optic axis has the
direction of the vertical crystallographic axis. All tetragonal and
hexagonal crystals are <xex>uniaxial</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Having only one axis; developing
along a single line or plane; -- opposed to
<xex>multiaxial</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uniaxially</ent>⟦br⟧
